Have you made any great videos using Google Earth?
Posted by mickmel at August 9, 2012 8:27 AM
Working with Idaho Rivers United I used the Google Earth Pro "Movie Maker" to record a 1920 x 1080 Image Stream sequence for this "Wild Boise River" video uploaded to YouTube.

Fraps is great and well worth the small price, but the main benefit with the GE Pro Movie Maker over Fraps is that it allows you to render a tour in non-realtime. Even with a powerful machine a tour with a lot of models or geometry will stutter a bit recorded playing in realtime - with Movie Maker you'll get perfect smooth framerate.
(it also lets you get the full 1920x1080 frame, GE doesn't maximize to the whole screen so Fraps will get a slightly smaller frame)
